HEADWORD: Tellurize
<hw>Tel"lu*rize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>To impregnate with, or to subject to the action of, tellurium; --
chiefly used adjectively in the past participle; <as>as,
<ex>tellurized</ex> ores</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tellurous</ent>⟦br⟧
